01/11/2004
ANKARA, Turkey -- The corruption trial of two former energy ministers -- Cumhur Ersumer and Zeki Cakan -- starts Tuesday (2 November) in Turkey's High Court.
They have been charged with violating public procurement regulations and conducting irregular deals in the natural gas sector.
Ersumer and Cakan served in Bulent Ecevit's cabinet from 1990 to 2002.
(NTV - 01/11/04)
